names.fullName: An interaction between VirE2 and VirD4 was demonstrated by cytology-based two-hybrid assay (C2H). VirD4, bait, fused to the half of green fluorescent protein (N'GFP) and VirE2, prey, fused to the other half of green fluorescent protein (GFP'C) were co-transformed into bacteria. Interactions were detected by fluorescence microscopy. Fig. 2A and B. VirD4-deltaN87-N'GFP interacted detectably with GFP'C-virE2. Fig. 3B. GFP'C-virE2[438-556], GFP'C-virE2[332-556], and GFP'C-virE2[85-556] interacted detectably with VirD4-N'GFP. Fig. 4A. GFP'C-virE2[484-556], GFP'C-virE2[1-438,534-556], GFP'C-virE2[1-520,534-556] and GFP'C-virE2[1-30,530-556] did not interact detectably with VirD4-N'GFP. Fig. 4A.

An interaction between VirE2 and VirD4 was demonstrated by co-immunoprecipitation. Endogenous VirE2 was immunoprecipitated from A348 (WT) cell extracts cross-linked with DSP using anti-E2 and precipitates were resolved by SDS-PAGE. Endogenous virD4 was detected by western blot using anti-D4. Fig. 3A. Anti-D4 co-immunoprecipitated VirE2 and VirD4 as detected by anti-E2. Fig. 3A.

names.fullName: An interaction between VirB7 and VirB9 was demonstrated by two dimensional SDS-PAGE and Western Blotting. Endogenous VirB7 and VirB9 both from Agrobacterium tumefaciens strain GV3850 (Tumorigenic T-DNA replaced with pBR322 amp gene) vir-induced with acetosyringone cell extracts were analyzed by two-dimensional SDS-PAGE. Cell extracts were lysed under nonreducing conditions and resolved by SDS-PAGE in the first dimension. Proteins from induced extracts were excised after first-dimension SDS-PAGE, incubated in Laemmli sample buffer with DTT and resolved by SDS-PAGE in the second dimension. Endogenous VirB7 and VirB9 was detected by western blot with VirB7 and VirB9 anti-serum respectively. Fig. 2.

The three dimensional structure of the Hypothetical Protein Q8u9w0 from Agrobacterium Tumefaciens. Northeast Structural Genomics Consortium Target Atr55 was determined by crystallography. The crystal was grown by hanging-drop and vapour diffusion using Hypothetical Protein Atu3615, 0.1m Na Citrate, PEG 20K (20%), at 293K. X-ray data were collected using synchrotron radiation and were 99.9% complete to a resolution limit of 2.500 angstroms. This crystal contained 7 chains per asymmetric unit and belonged to the space group C 2 2 21. The structure was determined using SAD and the modeled structure was refined to an R-factor = 20.9% and had an R-free = 26.7%. PDB: 1ZNP, MMDB: 33274.

names.fullName: An interaction between VirB2 and BTI1 was demonstrated by yeast two hybrid assay. VirB2[48-121], bait, fused to the LexA DNA binding domain (DBD) and BTI1, prey, fused to the GAL4 activation domain (AD) were sequentially-transformed into yeast strain CTY10-5d. Interactions were detected by beta-galactosidase activity. Fig. 1. The LexA-DBD-VirB2[48-121] interacted detectably with the truncation mutant GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-237, 261-275]. Fig. 4C. The LexA-DBD-VirB2[48-121] did not interact detectably with the truncation mutants GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-6, 108-275], GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-106, 141-275], GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-146, 181-275], GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-186, 232-275], GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-6], GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-106], GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-146] and GAL4-AD-BTI1[1-186]. Fig. 4C.

An interaction between VirB2 from an unspecified strain of Agrobacterium tumefaciens and BTI1 from Arabidopsis thaliana ecotype Columbia was demonstrated by GST pull-down assay. T7-BTI1 was isolated from E. coli BL21 (DE3) lysates using GST-VirB2 immobilized on glutathione-sepharose beads. Eluates were resolved by SDS-PAGE and analyzed by Western blot with anti-T7 tag antibodies. Fig. 2.
Component of type IV secretion system; pilin subunit.
